          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Do you use original parts?",
            "sub_head": "<p>Yes, around 90% of the parts we use are original Apple parts, disassembled from genuine Apple devices. We champion sustainable repairs, and reusing parts helps maintain Apple standards without creating unnecessary waste.</p><p>This approach means your MacBook retains features like True Tone, battery health monitoring, and the overall performance it was designed for after any repair at iCorrect.</p><p>The only exception is with older MacBook models, where it is no longer possible to source original batteries in high capacity condition. In those cases, we use the best quality OEM batteries available.</p>",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Do you repair damaged MacBook logic boards?",
            "sub_head": "<p>Yes, this is advanced work we are known for. While many repair centres, including Apple, will write off a faulty logic board and quote a full replacement, we repair them properly.</p><p>Our technicians work under a microscope, diagnosing issues at component and microchip level. That could mean anything from replacing a burned out MOSFET or shorted capacitor to rebuilding complete circuits after liquid damage. We revive boards others declare dead and we do it every day.</p><p>It is precise, delicate work, but it saves clients hundreds compared to Apple, keeps original data intact, and reduces electronic waste.</p><p>If Apple said your MacBook is not fixable and that you need a new one, there is a good chance we will prove them wrong.</p>",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "accordion",
