            "heading": "What if my MacBook repair does not resolve the issue?",
            "sub_head": "<p>It is rare, but if a repair does not fully resolve the problem your MacBook has, we will not charge you for it. Our no fix, no fee policy applies to all standard MacBook repairs, and we will always explain what went wrong and what your options are.</p><p>In more advanced logic board diagnostics, if we are unsuccessful, we will suggest an alternative like a logic board replacement or data recovery, depending on what we find.</p><p>Either way, you will get a clear answer, not guesswork. No surprises.</p>",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I get my MacBook repaired quicker?",
            "sub_head": "<p>Yes, we offer an Express MacBook Repair Service for clients who need a faster turnaround. This service is limited and subject to availability, so booking in advance is recommended.</p><p>When pre booked, express repairs are often completed within one working day, and in some cases, even the same day. This applies to most issues, including screen, battery, and logic board repairs. Express bookings are prioritised and priced accordingly.</p>",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What is your diagnostic process for MacBook repairs?",
            "sub_head": "<p>Diagnostics are where we do our best thinking. If the fault is not obvious, we run a full diagnostic on your MacBook, going deep into the logic board, charging system, and internal circuitry.</p><p>We perform a full power rail test and visual inspection under a microscope, looking for signs of damage at component level. That includes blown capacitors, corroded traces, and shorted chips. We then test each critical stage of the board to narrow down the fault.</p><p>Once we confirm the issue, we send a detailed report with a clear repair plan and quote so you are fully informed before any work begins.</p>",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "accordion",
